<item>
            <title>[CXF-5133] CXF STS renewed token not itself renewable.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5133</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When renewing a security token (a SAML assertion in my test case) the returned token cannot be renewed again (nor can the original).  This is true even if the &amp;lt;Renewing/&amp;gt; element is present in the renewal RST message.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that the SAMLTokenRenewer class does not put the STSConstants.TOKEN_RENEWING_ALLOW and STSConstants.TOKEN_RENEWING_ALLOW_AFTER_EXPIRY properties on the SecurityTOken placed in the token store, which are required for renewal to later take place.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP, Java 1.7&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
